article.headline: Georgia Tech 57, Georgia 42
article.story:
ATLANTA -- Iasia Hemingway scored 18 points, Brigitte Ardossi had 15 and Alex Montgomery added 11 to lead Georgia Tech to a 57-42 win over Georgia on Friday night, ending a three-game losing streak to its state rivals.

Georgia Tech (7-2), which is 6-0 at home, was coming off a 70-57 win over No. 21 Michigan State on Wednesday night.

The loss snapped a five-game winning streak by Georgia (7-2), but the Lady Bulldogs still lead the series with Tech 26-3. The Yellow Jackets have won three of the last six after losing the first 22.

Jaleesa Rhoden led Georgia with 13 points and Danielle Taylor added 12.
